{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":99301,"duration_api_ms":98803,"num_turns":18,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"9fbdafcc-dd97-4e99-9ef7-baebe762cacb","total_cost_usd":1.08563525,"usage":{"input_tokens":12,"cache_creation_input_tokens":86209,"cache_read_input_tokens":930488,"output_tokens":3261,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":86209,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":12,"outputTokens":3261,"cacheReadInputTokens":930488,"cacheCreationInputTokens":86209,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.08563525,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"evidence":["All 113 milestone_record tests pass (0 failures, 0 ignored) — verified by running cargo test --lib contexts::milestone_record","cargo clippy -- -D warnings passes cleanly (no warnings)","cargo fmt --all --check passes (no formatting issues)","Amendment fr-20-c613acbd FIXED: record_bead_start (service.rs:448-452) now writes structured JSON details via started_entry.start_journal_details() instead of the old format!('project={project_id}'). The start_journal_details method (model.rs:333-339) delegates to render_start_journal_details which serializes a StartJournalDetailsPayload struct containing project_id, run_id, and plan_hash.","model.rs:353-373 StartJournalDetailsPayload struct includes project_id (required), run_id (optional), and plan_hash (optional), serialized to JSON. Two BeadStarted events for the same bead/project/timestamp but different run_id or plan_hash now produce different details strings, preventing dedupe collision in append_event_if_missing.","fs.rs:2279-2324 StartJournalDetails struct with parse/merge/render methods. merge() (lines 2293-2315) rejects conflicting project_id/run_id/plan_hash, only allowing backfill of None→Some fields for same-attempt replay repair.","fs.rs:2470-2489 repairable_start_event() detects same-timestamp/same-bead BeadStarted events, parses their JSON details, and delegates to StartJournalDetails::merge. Conflicting run_id or plan_hash values cause merge to return None, so distinct named runs are NOT repaired/merged — they stay as separate journal rows.","fs.rs:2530-2534 append_event_if_missing now chains repairable_start_event alongside repairable_completion_event, so start events get the same repair-or-append treatment as completion events.","Test start_journal_dedupe_keeps_same_timestamp_named_attempts_separate (service.rs:4058-4156) verifies: start bead-1/project-1/run-2 at T, complete it, start bead-1/project-1/run-3 at same T — asserts exactly 2 distinct BeadStarted journal events with correct run_id values ('run-2' and 'run-3').","Test named_replay_with_matching_started_at_backfills_runless_attempt (service.rs:3883) verifies same-attempt start replay correctly backfills run_id without creating a duplicate journal row.","model.rs test start_journal_details_support_delimited_identifiers (line 1286) verifies JSON serialization safely handles identifiers with commas/delimiters.","All original acceptance criteria remain satisfied: milestone state answers 'what happened to bead X?' via find_runs_for_bead, controller can update linkage after each run outcome via update_task_run, backward compatibility maintained for legitimately optional fields"],"findings_or_gaps":["Amendment fr-20-c613acbd (BeadStarted journal dedupe collision) has been fully addressed in completion round 21. BeadStarted events now carry structured JSON details with project_id, run_id, and plan_hash, so distinct named runs produce different details strings even when they share a started_at timestamp. The dedupe key (timestamp, event_type, bead_id, details) now correctly distinguishes them.","The start event repair path (repairable_start_event) correctly handles same-attempt replays (backfilling run_id/plan_hash) while rejecting conflicting values that indicate distinct attempts — this is symmetric with how completion events are already handled.","AppError::RunStartFailed is still used (service.rs ~line 549) for rejecting non-terminal outcomes in update_task_run, which is semantically a finalization rejection. A more specific error variant would be cleaner but this is cosmetic, not a correctness issue — carried forward from prior reviews.","The outstanding risk — milestone mutations span separate lineage, snapshot, and journal files without a cross-file transaction — remains. All paths are serialized by the milestone mutation lock and replay-safe, making this an acceptable trade-off for file-based storage."],"follow_up_or_amendments":[],"outcome":"approved"},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"06bcca0a-0016-48d9-8192-47b2ad7dd756"}
